In his State of the Union address, President Biden congratulated members of Congress and highlighted the progress and resilience of the United States. He mentioned that the country has created a record 12 million new jobs in the past two years and that COVID no longer controls the lives of Americans. He also highlighted the strength of democracy and called for unity and bipartisanship in Congress. President Biden discussed the need to rebuild the middle class, invest in infrastructure, and create jobs. He emphasized the importance of affordable healthcare, including the need to lower prescription drug costs and expand access to mental health care. The President also addressed issues such as gun violence, immigration, climate change, and foreign policy, including the threat posed by China and the need to support Ukraine. He concluded by expressing his optimism for the future of America and the importance of coming together as a nation.